article.headline: Arkansas 86, North Texas 75
article.story: NORTH LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Michael Washington scored a career-high 34 points, and Arkansas went on a 21-2 run in the second half to pull away for a 86-75 win over North Texas on Saturday. Stefan Welsh added 19 points for Arkansas (11-1), which won its ninth straight. Washington also added 11 rebounds. Dominique Johnson scored 15 points for North Texas (8-6). The game was played at Alltel Arena, just across the Arkansas River from Little Rock. The Fayetteville-based Razorbacks had lost five of their previous seven games at Alltel. They trailed 42-40 at halftime and would have been down more if not for Washington. The 6-foot-9 junior scored 12 straight Arkansas points in one stretch and finished the half with 21.
